# Governance

## Audit Logs

Codex Enterprise and Claude Code Security ship audit logs.
Use `--output-format stream-json` when running Codex or Claude Code in CI
pipelines to produce structured, machine-readable audit trails.

## PR Labels

Every agent-authored pull request must carry the following GitHub labels:

| Label | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `agent-authored` | PR content was produced in whole or in part by an AI agent |
| `needs-human-review` | A human reviewer must approve before merge |

Apply both labels together on every agent-generated PR.

## Human Review Before Merge

No agent-authored PR may be merged without at least one human-approved review.
Agents commit to a branch; only humans merge to `<%= project.mainBranch %>`.

See the Git Rules section of [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) for the full branch,
commit-signing, and hook policy.

## CI Integration

Run Claude Code or Codex in CI with `--output-format stream-json` so that
every tool call and output is captured in the build log for post-hoc audit.
